Wednesday | 27th March, 2019
Wednesday | 27th March, 2019
New Delhi: The Aam Aadmi Party (AAP) on Wednesday announced the names of 15 star campaigners for the Lok Sabha polls in Delhi, with party chief and Chief Minister Arvind Kejriwal leading the team. “More names will be added in this list,” said AAP leader Gopal Rai, who also figures in the list. “There will be leaders from outside Delhi as well,” Rai said. Apart from Kejriwal and Rai, party leaders Manish Sisodia, Sanjay Singh, Bhagwant Mann, Sushil Gupta, N.D. Gupta, Satyendar Jain, Imran Hussain, Rajendra Pal Gautam, Kailash Gahlot, Saurabh Bharadwaj, Rakhi Birla, Jarnail Singh and Shahnaz Hindustani are in the list. Source: IANS
